<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6b7ba766-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s894b"><num value="894b">§ 894b.</num><heading> Rights of the victim of a sexual assault</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A victim of a sexual assault covered by the comprehensive policy developed under <ref href="/us/usc/t33/s894a/a">section 894a(a) of this title</ref> has the right to be reasonably protected from the accused.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6b7ba767-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/114/328/dC/tXXXV/s3543">Pub. L. 114–328, div. C, title XXXV, § 3543</ref>, <date date="2016-12-23">Dec. 23, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/2803">130 Stat. 2803</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
